<body>
    <h1>Get Rates</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p local-id=3D"c21ac52f236a"><strong>Component type:</strong> Actio=
n</p>
<p local-id=3D"5cf9f86cc9a2"><strong>Category:</strong> Spaces, Rates &amp;=
 Occupancy</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"c2a3a8c23ee4" id=3D"GetRates-Overview">Overview</h2>
<p local-id=3D"105f43db9cc4">The <strong>Get Rates</strong> action retrieve=
s all enabled rates configured in your property. This includes both public =
and private rates across all bookable services. The component returns a lis=
t of rate names and their unique identifiers, which can be used in subseque=
nt workflow steps =E2=80=94 for example, to filter reservations by rate, to=
 compare rates in a conditional branch, or to pass a specific rate ID into =
another action.</p>
<p local-id=3D"9c7524190e17">This component has no input fields. When trigg=
ered, it automatically fetches all available rates for the property associa=
ted with your connection and outputs them as a list on the <strong>out</str=
ong> port.</p>
<p local-id=3D"d69a3339dad4"><strong>Note:</strong> Only <strong>enabled</s=
trong> rates are returned. Disabled rates and voucher rates are excluded fr=
om the results.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"4081a094-734a-436c-aae3-7839887b9038">
<h2 local-id=3D"4447576e8b59" id=3D"GetRates-InputFields">Input Fields</h2>
<p local-id=3D"4975c3b54cbc">This component has <strong>no input fields</st=
rong>. It automatically retrieves all enabled rates for the property linked=
 to the authenticated connection. Simply connect it to a preceding step in =
your workflow to trigger it.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"7b61b3ba-dfb8-497c-be44-3f9123ee4976">
<h2 local-id=3D"1f60ba78e60f" id=3D"GetRates-OutputFields">Output Fields</h=
2>
<p local-id=3D"41674d29678a">When the rates are successfully retrieved, the=
 following values are available on the <strong>out</strong> output port. Th=
e output is a list (array), where each item represents one rate:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"2eae2325-28f6-4616-a6a3-edf=
a3557b6f9" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"5a8868de-01f1-49af-90a3-403235d4a074">
<th data-local-id=3D"da9b6eea-8032-4674-8ddd-147ef42060ad" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"da0bec048c63">Field</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"3aa233f2-406c-4630-97f0-6ac1cd0fab1a" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"36ad0d71292d">Type</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"46cfb045-8795-495e-ba99-ba0d564e3562" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"5b0db79e94d1">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"cb8c9215-ac8c-44f3-bf07-a7d0b24b1adc">
<td data-local-id=3D"bffa9b14-a000-4bf6-acfd-5897d2f5b1ef" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"391a67414147"><strong>Value</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"a77df88b-29da-4f73-9848-7d8220bfcbc8" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c571f8a6b313">Text (GUID)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"587c4194-d234-41f6-ba00-25022be1c87f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a7e09c55c090">The unique identifier of the rate. Use this ID=
 when passing a rate into other components (e.g., filtering reservations by=
 rate).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"1b94e9c1-bfe0-4b49-bc9f-f4817274b9fd">
<td data-local-id=3D"8ae94f1f-b2cd-4779-8e18-16ae3c4202b6" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"eecb11f42bb2"><strong>Label</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"38e9a722-7d35-493a-a834-2946571ee6ef" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ff0969f109e1">Text</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"78678459-082a-4412-8c36-5e8fe2ef21cf" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a779f8277bd0">The display name of the rate in the property's=
 default language. If the property has multiple bookable services, the serv=
ice name is appended in parentheses to distinguish rates across services =
=E2=80=94 for example, <code>Best Available Rate (Accommodation)</code>.</p=
></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"bb02a664eed2"><strong>Tip:</strong> The output list is order=
ed by the rate ordering configured in your property settings, so the rates =
appear in the same order as they do in Mews Operations.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"b6dcf373-e578-4226-8309-a71f09ba0d85">
<h2 local-id=3D"60b6e8150f41" id=3D"GetRates-HowItWorks">How It Works</h2>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"967a7f20-d0ee-43fa-abba-9060c046275e">
<li local-id=3D"7ff00610-3894-43f2-9d5d-07e901b7161c">
<p local-id=3D"1c24b956fff2">The component receives a trigger from the prev=
ious step in the workflow.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ad3c91d8-c1a8-4b70-bf7d-0d66a2a93007">
<p local-id=3D"cb2d77798c2a">A request is sent to retrieve all enabled rate=
s (public and private) across all bookable services configured in the prope=
rty.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"adef87b9-9723-41a0-9e40-7a91785c7f1d">
<p local-id=3D"e07423adce61">Voucher rates and disabled rates are automatic=
ally excluded from the results.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"61880324-958c-4991-b465-df273626fc9e">
<p local-id=3D"2804fd4648af">Each rate is returned with its display name. I=
f the property has more than one bookable service, the service name is appe=
nded to each rate name to help distinguish them (e.g., <code>Standard Rate =
(Accommodation)</code> vs. <code>Standard Rate (Spa)</code>).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ccde32b7-d3e0-430d-8daa-e20bf86daeb0">
<p local-id=3D"098c687fc646">The list of rates is sorted by the ordering de=
fined in the property configuration and sent to the <strong>out</strong> ou=
tput port.</p></li>
</ol>
<hr local-id=3D"1f46fa93-876e-4c39-aad5-1f56dceea5e4">
<h2 local-id=3D"9e4a479f0e1b" id=3D"GetRates-ExampleUseCases">Example Use C=
ases</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"3b117755-2c31-482f-97e7-98c7664b278b">
<li local-id=3D"7aac551c-6fee-4423-aec9-781a69f513fb">
<p local-id=3D"f3fa328cfeff"><strong>Rate-based routing</strong> =E2=80=94 =
Retrieve all rates and use them in a conditional branch to apply different =
logic depending on which rate a reservation was booked with (e.g., send a w=
elcome email only for "Best Available Rate" bookings).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c1523744-af7a-4f4c-8b64-78df5cad6867">
<p local-id=3D"ac40db4b287a"><strong>Populating a dropdown</strong> =E2=80=
=94 Use the output as a dynamic data source to populate rate selection drop=
downs in other components within your workflow.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0b3bd575-86fd-4ac9-8816-86079e5efb36">
<p local-id=3D"c8a741da047d"><strong>Rate auditing</strong> =E2=80=94 Perio=
dically fetch all enabled rates to verify that the expected rates are activ=
e and correctly configured in the property.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"26451795-c395-418f-a13d-94fb33105fae">
<h2 local-id=3D"33e83dfc5a49" id=3D"GetRates-ErrorHandling">Error Handling<=
/h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"e436d2e3-68f6-400a-9ad9-68e=
5eaa309c9" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"2008e258-59c9-46b8-a143-9d5751ecb90e">
<th data-local-id=3D"0f91e512-97fd-413e-a3b9-ff9a5af84576" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"af1c93783420">Error</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"840247c7-a12d-46dc-aa02-d3fe0e05be67" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"4b5d3a42e018">Cause</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"31007094-67a1-4569-8871-f05deda66620">
<td data-local-id=3D"4f799831-9289-4566-9464-165b9da21183" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"609953ff7a8f"><code>Request failed with status code {code}.<=
/code></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"3447c807-6fb4-4e76-b1b3-f658e09027e2" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4c5e400a4324">The request to retrieve rates failed. This may=
 indicate an authentication issue with the connection or a temporary servic=
e disruption.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
